The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Murali named deputy
                                                                                                                       7                                      Murali named deputy
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Test crickets most successful bowler Muttiah Muralidharan, who will play his final Test, against India, at Galle, from July 18, has been named as Kumar Sangakkaras deputy.         
	According to a media release from Sri Lanka Cricket, a 16-member squad has been named for the first of three Tests.         
	The Test Squad         
	Kumar Sangakkara (captain), Muttiah Muralidharan (vice-captain), T.M. Dilshan, Tharanga Paranawithana, Mahela Jayawardene, Thilan Samaraweera, Anjelo Mathews, Prasanna Jayawardene, Lasith Malinga, Rangana Herath, Dilhara Fernando, Dhammika Prasad, Suraj Randiv, Thilina Kandamby, Chanaka Welagedara, Lahiru Thirimanna.                                                                                                                     
